items.name: case accessRestricted
items.desc: An error that indicates the system configuration restricts access to the asset.

items.name: case accessUserDenied
items.desc: An error that indicates the user denies access.

items.name: case changeNotSupported
items.desc: An error that indicates the system doesn’t support the change request as configured.

items.name: case identifierNotFound
items.desc: An error that indicates an identifier doesn’t exist.

items.name: case internalError
items.desc: An error that indicates an internal error occured.

items.name: case invalidResource
items.desc: An error that indicates the asset resource validation fails.

items.name: case libraryVolumeOffline
items.desc: An error that indicates the photo library isn’t available because the file system volume that stores it isn’t mounted.

items.name: case missingResource
items.desc: An error that indicates a missing asset resource.

items.name: case multipleIdentifiersFound
items.desc: An error that indicates that more than one identifiers exist.

items.name: case networkAccessRequired
items.desc: An error that indicates the request for an asset resource fails because it requires network access.

items.name: case notEnoughSpace
items.desc: An error that indicates there’s not enough space to perform the requested change.

items.name: case operationInterrupted
items.desc: An error that indicates an interruption occured and couldn’t complete.

items.name: case relinquishingLibraryBundleToWriter
items.desc: An error that indicates the photo library isn’t available because the user moved, renamed, or deleted the system’s photo library.

items.name: case requestNotSupportedForAsset
items.desc: An error that indicates the system doesn’t support the request for the specified asset.

items.name: case switchingSystemPhotoLibrary
items.desc: An error that indicates the photo library isn’t available because the user switches the system’s photo library.

items.name: case userCancelled
items.desc: An error that indicates the user cancels the asset retrieval or editing request.
